      • invokeDBtoJMSservlet

        public java.lang.Long invokeDBtoJMSservlet(java.net.Socket socket,
                                           java.lang.String hostName,
                                           java.lang.String contextRoot,
                                           java.lang.String hostEncoding,
                                           java.lang.String username,
                                           java.lang.String passwordEncr,
                                           boolean traceEnabled)
                                    throws AppRuntimeException
        Invokes the DBtoJMS servlet to initiate a transfer.
        Parameters:
        socket - The already opened socket to the target server.
        hostName - The target host name.
        contextRoot - The context root of the application.
        hostEncoding - The string encoding used by the server.
        username - The user name to invoke the method under.
        passwordEncr - The encrypted password for this user.
        traceEnabled - Specifies whether tracing should be enabled for trouble shooting.
        Returns:
        The instance data ID for the deferred process if successful, or zero if the request did not complete.
        Throws:
        AppRuntimeException - If an error occurred during triggering.
